    ns1:inpersonHours "30 horas (38.5%)"@es ;
    ns1:numberOfCredits 3.0 ;
    ns1:otherInformation """ADDENDUM TO THE LEARNING OUTCOMES DECLARATION (RD 822/2021)
The course also contributes to the following abilities:
H.13: Ability to apply techniques and methods for complex problem-solving in engineering practice, developing projects under professional analysis and synthesis.
H.14: Application of materials, equipment, technology, and engineering processes in their engineering field.
H.16: Conscious assumption of social, health and safety, environmental, and economic implications of industrial engineering practice.

SUSTAINABLE DEVELOPMENT GOALS
Contribution of the course to the following SDG:
SDG 9: Industry, innovation and infrastructure.
SDG 12: Responsible consumption and production.

TYPE: Skills or abilities
H9. Project, design and develop complex products (parts, components, finished products, etc.), processes and systems of their specialty, which meet the established requirements, including being aware of social, health and safety, environmental, economic and social aspects. industrial; as well as select and apply appropriate project methods, using some cutting-edge knowledge where appropriate.
H13. Practice with applicable techniques and methods to solve complex problems, carry out complex engineering projects and carry out inquiry, analysis and synthesis, also considering their limitations, within the scope of their specialty.
H14. Apply materials, equipment and tools, technology and engineering processes and their limitations within the scope of their specialty."""@es ;
    ns1:periodEndingMonth "Enero"@es ;
    ns1:periodStartingMonth "Septiembre"@es ;
    ns1:teachingPeriod "2025-26" ;
    ns1:teachingPeriodMonths "Septiembre-Enero"@es ;
    ns1:totalHours "30 horas"@es ;
    schema:activitiesWorkload "100%"@es ;
    schema:courseSchedule <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/565005803/2025-26/eventSchedule> ;
    schema:description """Mechatronics engineering is an integrated discipline that focuses on the design and analysis of complete engineering systems. It is an area that merges concepts from at least four different disciplines: industrial design, mechanical engineering, electronic and electrical engineering and software engineering.
This course aims to introduce the student to the multidisciplinary challenge required by modern mechatronic systems. At the end of the course, students will be able to propose integrated, innovative, efficient and environmentally sustainable solutions to technical problems that require the interaction of these disciplines.

To evaluate and select suitable actuators, sensors, controllers, and algorithms.
To integrate components and subsystems.
To follow a well-defined mechatronics design procedure.
To be able to propose a reliable and suitable mechatronic solution taking into consideration quality and environmental awareness.

Main learnign outcomes:

Analyses the all requirements of the problems since mechatronics point of view.
Ability to design and develop a basic mechatronic system.
Select the suitable components for a mechatronic problem and integrate them.
Ability to understand a mechatronic system.
Ability to communicate efficiently the outcome of the solution process and analysis."""@es ;
    schema:director <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/cecilia.garcia%40upm.es> ;
    schema:inLanguage "Inglés/Castellano"@es ;
    schema:instructor <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/cecilia.garcia%40upm.es> ;
    schema:name "Introduction To Mechatronic Systems Design"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/565005803/2025-26/C.11.5.> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "C.11.5." ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Conocer en detalle los sensores y actuadores más utilizados en los sistemas mecatrónicos actuales y seleccionar los elementos más adecuados, junto al software y hardware para la adquisición de datos y control de los sistemas mecatrónicos. Conocimiento aplicado de la interacción e integración de los sistemas mecatrónicos con el entorno y el ser humano. TIPO: Conocimientos o contenidos."@es .

